1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,920
(YELLS)

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:05,000
It is.

3
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:06,960
It's you two.

4
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:08,800
We could say hi to Future Us.

5
00:00:11,840 --> 00:00:14,480
- (AMY SHRIEKS)
- Get away!

6
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:16,040
Amy, no! No!

7
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:23,760
- Go! Go!
- Her name's Alaya.

8
00:00:23,840 --> 00:00:25,480
She's one of their warriors.

9
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:26,960
One of you will kill me.

10
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:29,280
- If she lives, so do Elliot...
- Mum...

11
00:00:29,360 --> 00:00:30,680
...and Mo...

12
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:32,640
and Amy, because I will find them.

13
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:35,000
My death shall ignite a war

14
00:00:35,080 --> 00:00:37,680
and every stinking ape
shall be wiped from the surface

15
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:39,880
of my beloved planet.

16
00:00:39,960 --> 00:00:41,920
We return their hostage,
they return ours.

17
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,560
Nobody dies today.

18
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:24,000
ELDANE: This is the story
of our planet, Earth,

19
00:01:24,080 --> 00:01:25,960
of the day 1,000 years past

20
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:29,280
when we came to share it
with a race known as Humanity.

21
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:34,160
It is the story of the Doctor who
helped our races find common ground

22
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:36,280
and the terrible losses he suffered.

23
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:40,320
It is the story of our past
and must never be forgotten.

24
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,480
This place is enormous and deserted.

25
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:45,480
The majority of the race
are probably still asleep.

26
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:48,600
We need to find Amy, looking
for heat signature anomalies.

27
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:50,640
But, Doctor, how can all this be here?

28
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:52,440
I mean, these plants.

29
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:55,480
Must be getting closer
to the centre of the city.

30
00:01:57,160 --> 00:02:00,400
You're sure
this is the best way to enter?

31
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:02,840
Front door approach!
Definitely. Always the best way...

32
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:05,440
PA: Hostile life force detected, area 17.

33
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,840
Apart from the back door approach,
that's also good,

34
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,440
sometimes better.

35
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:12,280
- Hostile life force detected, area 17.
- Doctor?

36
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:16,320
Hostile life force detected, area 17.

37
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,440
We're not hostile, we're not armed!

38
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:19,920
We're here in peace!

39
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:24,320
(THEY COUGH)

40
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:29,480
(WHIMPERING)

41
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:32,480
Don't you come near me with that!

42
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,960
(WHIMPERING)

43
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:37,240
(GROANING)

44
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:40,320
From the clothing,

45
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:44,120
the human female appears to be
more resistant to the cold

46
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:45,160
than the male.

47
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,440
I dressed for Rio!

48
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:49,600
Leave her alone! You've got me/

49
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:52,160
- (CLUNKING)
- (SHRIEKS)

50
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:54,200
Decontamination complete.

51
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:57,680
Commencing dissection.

52
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:00,760
(WHIMPERS)

53
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:05,680
PA: Area 17 incursion,
species diagnostic requested.

54
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:08,800
Area 17 incursion,
species diagnostic requested.

55
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:11,360
Yeah! And stay out!

56
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:19,960
Ha-ha!

57
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,320
How did you get that?

58
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:27,760
You never picked a lizard man's
pocket? Come on, before he gets back.

59
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:30,400
That creature,
do you think it was an alien?

60
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:32,440
Any more of them, do you think?

61
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:34,480
Do you think the Earth's been invaded?

62
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:37,360
Don't know. But I know someone
who could have some answers.

63
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,600
We need to get back to the surface
and find him.

64
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,840
- I wonder where this leads.
- Maybe it's a way out.

65
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,960
- Oh, my God, no.
- What is it?

66
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:55,160
Oh, God...

67
00:03:55,240 --> 00:04:00,320
It's my son. It's Elliot.
What've they done to him?

68
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,680
No! He's in there!
We have to get him out!

69
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:05,520
Elliot! Elliot, it's Dad!

70
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:08,480
PA: Access denied.
Unauthorised genetic imprint.

71
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:09,800
Stop. Seriously. We can't get in.

72
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:11,080
That's my boy in there!

73
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:13,920
These screens, they're monitoring
something. I think they're vital signs -

74
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,040
heartbeats, pulses.
Why else would he be wired up?

75
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:19,040
- He's still alive.
- All right.

76
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:21,640
We find weapons,
get that creature from the lab

77
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:23,760
and force it to release Elliot, yeah?

78
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:27,280
Yeah, trust me. We'll get him out.

79
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:40,320
Ambrose.

80
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:44,360
You lied.
You told us you were the police.

81
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:46,480
It was a misunderstanding...

82
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:52,040
Who are you? You and the Doctor?
Why is this happening to us?

83
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:53,480
What did we ever do?

84
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:57,200
The Doctor will get your son back,
I promise. In the meantime,

85
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:58,920
we take turns guarding the creature.

86
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,600
So that's it? We just sit and wait.

87
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:03,240
And then we exchange her
for your family.

88
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:07,240
I promise you, Ambrose,
I'd trust the Doctor with my life.

89
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:08,920
We stick to his plan.

90
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:12,080
We keep that creature safe.

91
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:19,000
Argh! Argh!

92
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:22,640
How can they have escaped?

93
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:27,000
This proves all prisoners
should remain under military guard.

94
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:32,760
I'm sure you'd prefer to be in charge
of everything and everyone, Restac,

95
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:35,960
but we rank the same.

96
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,920
(SCREAMING)

97
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,760
Is there any word from Alaya?

98
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:41,080
No.

99
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:44,000
It's fine to show concern, you know.

100
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:48,000
- She's part of your gene-chain.
- Huh!

101
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:50,280
I'm decontaminating now.

102
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:53,800
(ELECTRONIC BUZZING)

103
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:56,160
Decontamination? No, no, no!

104
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,480
(DOCTOR YELLS)

105
00:05:57,560 --> 00:06:01,320
- (BUZZING RISES IN PITCH)
- (DOCTOR SCREAMS)

106
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:12,160
(SNIFFS)

107
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:19,520
Why aren't you dead? You're
carrying my venom in your blood.

108
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,800
You should have died.
Why aren't you dead?

109
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:23,760
Show me.

110
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:28,080
(HISSES)

111
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:32,920
- How does it feel, ape?
- Like it's burning in my blood.

112
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,640
Please.

113
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:37,480
If you help me, I can help you.

114
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:40,400
If you could cure me,
I could help you escape.

115
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:45,080
You see? You beg
and offer betrayal so early!

116
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:49,440
Why would I want to escape
when I can watch you die?

117
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:53,840
The first ape death of the coming war.

118
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:02,560
(DOCTOR YELLS)

119
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:04,920
Its all right. It won't harm you.

120
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,640
I'm only neutralising
all your ape bacteria.

121
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:08,640
I'm not an ape! Look at the scans!

122
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:11,960
Two hearts!
Totally different! Totally not ape!

123
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:17,640
Remove all human germs, you remove
half the things keeping me alive.

124
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,280
No, complete the process.

125
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:26,080
Oh, that's much better, thanks!

126
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:28,480
Not got any celery, have you?

127
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:31,240
No, no, not really the climate.

128
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:34,720
Tomatoes, though, you'd do
a roaring trade in those. I'm the Doctor.

129
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:39,000
Oh, and there's Nasreen, good!

130
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:41,120
Oh, a green man.

131
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:44,160
Hello, who are you?

132
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:46,120
Restac. Military commander.

133
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,640
Oh, dear, really?

134
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:49,840
There's always a military, isn't there?

135
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:54,520
Your weapon was attacking
the oxygen pockets above our city.

136
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:55,720
Oxygen pockets! Lovely!

137
00:07:55,800 --> 00:08:00,200
Oooh, but not so good
with an impending drill!

138
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,880
Now it makes sense!

139
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:04,480
Where is the rest of your invasion force?

140
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:05,880
Invasion force?

141
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:10,880
Me and lovely Nasreen? No!
We came for the humans you took.

142
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:15,480
And...to offer the safe return of Alaya.

143
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:20,400
Oh, wait, you and she,
what is it, same genetic source?

144
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:23,080
Of course you're worried,
but don't be, she's safe.

145
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:26,360
You claim to come in peace,

146
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:28,720
but you hold one of us hostage.

147
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:31,160
Wait, wait, we all want
the same thing here.

148
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,520
I don't negotiate with apes.

149
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:35,400
I'm going to send a clear message
to those on the surface.

150
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:37,440
What's that?

151
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:39,920
Your execution.

152
00:08:41,680 --> 00:08:43,360
Yes...

153
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:49,680
These chambers are all over the city.

154
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:57,960
Uh! Turn it off quick!

155
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:01,880
- They're not moving.
- Maybe they're asleep.

156
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:03,000
Let's have another look.

157
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:05,880
No, Amy, don't!

158
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:16,440
Amy, what are you doing?
Get out of there.

159
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:23,720
(WHISPERS) Some sort
of suspended animation.

160
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:30,280
I wonder what these are.

161
00:09:31,880 --> 00:09:36,480
The Doctor would know.
The Doctor always knows.

162
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:37,840
Hey, look.

163
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,440
Wait...

164
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,880
I've got it.

165
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:46,520
It's how they came up to the surface.

166
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:50,280
Some sort of powered transport discs.
It's our way out of here.

167
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:54,680
Even better, weapons.
Come on, now we can fight back.

168
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:08,320
- Which way now?
- Door at the end.

169
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:09,920
- Are you sure?
- Nope!

170
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:22,640
- MO: Wow.
- AMY: Yeah.

171
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:25,760
We don't stand a chance.

172
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:27,400
We have to find the Doctor.

173
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:46,800
Dad, are you all right? Dad!

174
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,920
Ambrose, I'm fine! Leave me alone.

175
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,520
You are not fine. Let me...

176
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:54,560
Let me look.

177
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:55,880
Get off!

178
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:56,840
Let me look.

179
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:07,360
Oh, my God, Dad.

180
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:09,280
I don't know what's happening to me.

181
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:13,960
It's going to be fine.

182
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:19,120
First thing is bring
this temperature down, get you resting.

183
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:30,120
These must be the only ones awake.

184
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:32,480
The others must still be
in hibernation.

185
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:35,520
So, why did they go into
hibernation in the first place?

186
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,080
Their astronomers predicted

187
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:39,520
the planet heading to Earth
on a crash course.

188
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,560
They built a life underground
and put themselves to sleep

189
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:45,080
for millennia in order to avert what
they thought was the apocalypse.

190
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:47,320
When in reality, it was the moon

191
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:50,200
coming into alignment
with the Earth.

192
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:56,120
How can you know that?

193
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:59,200
Long time ago, I met another
tribe of Homo reptilia,

194
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:03,880
- similar, but not identical.
- Others of our species have survived?

195
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:09,240
The humans attacked them.

196
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:11,320
They died, I'm sorry.

197
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:19,680
A vermin race.

198
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:28,720
- What's the cure?
- What?

199
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:31,280
I saw what you've done to my dad.

200
00:12:32,880 --> 00:12:34,480
What's the cure?

201
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:36,800
Why would I tell you?

202
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:39,360
Cos if you don't,

203
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:44,160
I'm going to have to use this on you.

204
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:45,960
Now you reveal yourselves.

205
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:48,880
First you take my son,
now you hurt my dad.

206
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:51,520
I'm just protecting my family here.

207
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:54,640
That's all. I don't want to use it.

208
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:57,320
I want you to put things right.

209
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:58,960
Use it.

210
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:00,520
What?

211
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,120
Use it on me.

212
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:05,360
But you're too afraid.

213
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:13,440
A woman who can't even protect
her own child must be too weak to...

214
00:13:13,520 --> 00:13:16,920
- (ZAPPING, SHE SHRIEKS)
- I didn't want to do that.

215
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:20,520
Are you all right? Tell me,
what's the cure for my dad?

216
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:23,080
He's vermin. He deserves a painful death.

217
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:24,920
I'm giving you a chance.

218
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,520
I knew it would be you.

219
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:29,400
The one with the most
to lose, the weakest.

220
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:31,920
(ZAPPING)

221
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:39,640
I'm a nurse,
you should've told me.

222
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:42,720
(SCREAMING IN DISTANCE)

223
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:47,960
(ALAYA GASPS FOR BREATH)

224
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:53,880
- Ambrose... What have you done?
- She kept taunting me

225
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:56,040
about Mo and Elliot and you.

226
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:58,080
(ALAYA GROANS)

227
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:04,360
We have to be better than this!

228
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:05,960
She wouldn't tell me anything.

229
00:14:06,040 --> 00:14:08,960
I thought sooner or later,
she'd give in. I would've done.

230
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:13,240
I just... I just want my family back, Dad.

231
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:15,320
RORY: I'm sorry.

232
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:17,720
How do we help you?
Tell us what to do.

233
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:19,760
I knew this would come.

234
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:23,560
And soon the war.

235
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:25,680
You're not dying.

236
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:28,320
I'm not going to let you,
not today...

237
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:31,240
(ALAYA GROANS LOUDLY)

238
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:47,800
You're not authorised to do this!

239
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:51,280
I'm authorised to protect the safety
of our species while they sleep.

240
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:53,400
THE DOCTOR: Oh, lovely place,
very gleaming.

241
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:58,520
This is our court
and our place of execution.

242
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:04,480
- Let them go!
- Amy Pond, there's a girl to rely on.

243
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:09,520
You're covered both ways,
so don't try anything clever, buster.

244
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:15,000
- Mo!
- Now let them go. Or I shoot.

245
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:16,840
I'm warning you!

246
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:20,360
- Don't you touch her!
- And you?

247
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:25,760
All right, Restac.
You've made your point.

248
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:33,760
This is now a military tribunal.

249
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:36,360
Go back to your laboratory,
Malohkeh.

250
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:47,320
This isn't the way.

251
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:53,520
Prepare them for execution.

252
00:15:57,040 --> 00:16:01,080
OK, sorry, as rescues go,
didn't live up to its potential.

253
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:03,520
- I'm glad you're OK.
- Me too!

254
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:06,440
Lizard men, though!

255
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:09,360
Homo reptilia- they occupied
the planet before humans.

256
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:10,880
Now they want it back.

257
00:16:10,960 --> 00:16:14,120
After they've wiped out the human race.

258
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:17,960
Right, preferred it
when I didn't know, to be honest.

259
00:16:18,040 --> 00:16:20,440
NASREEN: Why are they waiting?

260
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:23,120
What do you think
they're going to do with us?

261
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:33,280
I didn't know it would go like that, Dad.

262
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:39,360
Oh, my little girl,
what have you done?

263
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:44,000
What happens now?

264
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:45,520
(BUZZING)

265
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:52,640
Oh, my God.

266
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:54,440
Who is the ape leader?

267
00:16:54,520 --> 00:17:01,280
It's them. How are they doing that?
How do they know that we're in here?

268
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:04,160
Who speaks for the apes?

269
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:12,200
Don't tell them what's happened.

270
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:18,880
I speak for the...

271
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:21,920
humans. Some of us, anyway.

272
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,440
Do you understand who we are?

273
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:27,520
Sort of. A bit. Not really.

274
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:30,920
We have ape hostages.

275
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:34,000
- Doctor! Amy!
- Mo! |

276
00:17:34,080 --> 00:17:36,160
Mo, are you OK?

277
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:38,960
I'm fine, love! I've found Elliot.
I'm bringing him home!

278
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:41,160
Amy, I thought I'd lost you!

279
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:45,560
What, cos I was sucked into the ground?
You're so clingy.

280
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:47,680
- Tony Mack!
- Having fun down there?

281
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:52,440
Not to interrupt, but
Just a quick reminder to stay calm.

282
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:54,320
Show me Alaya.

283
00:17:57,880 --> 00:18:03,680
Show me and release her, immediately,
unharmed, or we kill your friends

284
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:05,760
one by one.

285
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:07,880
- No!
- Ambrose...

286
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:09,080
Steady now, everyone.

287
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:12,440
- Ambrose, stop it/
- Get off me, Dad/!

288
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:15,800
- We didn't start this!
- Let Rory deal with this, Ambrose, eh?

289
00:18:15,880 --> 00:18:19,240
We are not doing what you say any more.

290
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:22,120
Now, give me back my family!

291
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:32,360
No.

292
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:35,200
Execute the girl.

293
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:36,960
No! No, wait!

294
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:39,120
- Rory!
- She's not speaking for us!

295
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:41,840
- There's no need for this...
- Listen!

296
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,520
- Aim.
- Whatever you want, we'll do it!

297
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:44,320
- Amy!
- Rory!

298
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:46,800
- Don't do this.
- No!

299
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:49,240
- Fire!
- Stop!

300
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:58,320
You want to start a war
while the rest of us sleep, Restac?

301
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:00,080
The apes are attacking us!

302
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:06,320
You're our protector, not our commander,
Restac. Unchain them.

303
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:10,960
I do not recognise
your authority at this time, Eldane.

304
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:14,720
Well, then, you must shoot me.

305
00:19:20,320 --> 00:19:22,680
You woke him to undermine me.

306
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:25,600
We're not monsters
and neither are they.

307
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:28,880
What is it about apes
you love so much? Mmm?

308
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:32,960
While you slept, they've evolved.
I've seen it for myself.

309
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:35,240
We used to hunt apes for sport.

310
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:40,160
When we came underground,
they bred and polluted this planet.

311
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:42,720
Shush now, Restac.

312
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:46,440
Go and play soldiers.
I'll let you know if I need you.

313
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:51,480
You'll need me,

314
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:53,240
then we'll see.

315
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:56,640
Nothing!

316
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:58,680
I've got to get down there.

317
00:19:58,760 --> 00:20:01,720
- Rory! Hello!
- Where's Amy?

318
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:04,640
- She's fine, look, here she is.
- Oh, thank God.

319
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:07,120
- Keeping you on your toes!
- No time to chat.

320
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:10,040
Listen, you need to get down here.

321
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:12,440
Go to the drill storeroom.
There's a large patch of earth

322
00:20:12,520 --> 00:20:13,640
in the middle of the floor.

323
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:17,920
The Silurians are going to send up
transport discs to bring you back down

324
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:20,280
using geothermal energy
and gravity-bubble technology.

325
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:24,080
It's how they travel and, frankly,
it's pretty cool. Bring Alaya.

326
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:27,960
We hand her over, we can land this
after all. All going to work, promise.

327
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:30,480
Got to dash! Hurry up!

328
00:20:30,560 --> 00:20:34,560
The moment we get down there,
everything will fall apart.

329
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:36,120
We have to return her.

330
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:42,120
They deserve at least that.

331
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:44,480
I'd say you've got
a fair bit to talk about.

332
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:46,160
- How so?
- You both want the planet.

333
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:47,920
You both have a genuine claim to it.

334
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:52,120
Are you authorised to negotiate
on behalf of humanity?

335
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:54,640
Me? No!
But they are!

336
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:57,800
- What?!
- No, we're not!

337
00:20:57,920 --> 00:21:01,360
Course you are! Amy Pond and Nasreen
Chaudhry, speaking for the planet!

338
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:03,360
Humanity couldn't have
better ambassadors.

339
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:06,520
Come on, who has more fun than us?

340
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:09,760
Is this what happens, in the future,
the planet gets shared?

341
00:21:09,840 --> 00:21:12,680
- Is that what we need to do?
- What are you talking about?

342
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:14,280
Oh, Nasreen, sorry,

343
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:18,160
probably worth mentioning at this stage,
Amy and I travel in time, a bit.

344
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:19,800
Anything else?

345
00:21:22,520 --> 00:21:24,520
There are fixed points through time,

346
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:27,040
where things must always
stay the way they are.

347
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:28,320
This is not one of them.

348
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:31,280
This is an opportunity,
a temporal tipping point.

349
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:34,600
Whatever happens today
will change future events,

350
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:36,520
create its own timeline,
its own reality.

351
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:40,440
The future pivots around you.
Here. Now.

352
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:42,240
So do good.

353
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:46,360
For humanity, and for Earth.

354
00:21:48,360 --> 00:21:50,320
Right.
No pressure there, then(!)

355
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:53,400
We can't share the planet.

356
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:55,760
Nobody on the surface
is going to go for this idea.

357
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:59,320
- It is just too big a leap!
- Come on.

358
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:01,640
Be extraordinary.

359
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:04,600
Oh...you...

360
00:22:10,280 --> 00:22:11,760
OK.

361
00:22:14,320 --> 00:22:19,480
Bringing things to order -
the first meeting of representatives

362
00:22:19,560 --> 00:22:23,600
of the human race and Homo reptilia
is now in session.

363
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:28,480
Ha! Never said that before,
that's fab! Carry on!

364
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:32,160
Now, Mo, let's go and get your son.

365
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:36,120
Oh, you know, humans and their
predecessors, shooting the breeze.

366
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:37,760
Never thought I'd see it.

367
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:45,600
So we get on those, and they
take us down through the Earth?

368
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:49,720
Geothermal gravity bubbles,
or something.

369
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:51,400
They sent four.

370
00:22:51,480 --> 00:22:55,280
She was our only bargaining chip.

371
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:57,760
We have to hand her back.

372
00:22:57,840 --> 00:22:59,880
Wait...

373
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:03,000
Before we go down,
there's something I've got to do...

374
00:23:03,080 --> 00:23:07,120
Dad, I need your help.

375
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:09,040
- No! No way.
- Please, Dad...

376
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:12,280
- just a precaution.
- I've told you, I won't do it.

377
00:23:12,360 --> 00:23:15,160
- Look at what they did to you!
- This isn't about me or you.

378
00:23:15,240 --> 00:23:16,800
No, it's about your grandson.

379
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:19,360
If you won't do it for me,
do it for Elliot.

380
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:22,840
I know I did wrong.

381
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:24,400
But I can't lose him, Dad.

382
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:34,640
Elliot, there you are.

383
00:23:38,240 --> 00:23:40,840
- If you've harmed him in any way.
- Of course not!

384
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:43,600
- I only store the young.
- But why?

385
00:23:43,680 --> 00:23:46,120
I took samples of the young,

386
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:49,080
slowed their lifecycles
to a millionth of their normal rate,

387
00:23:49,160 --> 00:23:51,600
so I could study how they grew,
what they needed,

388
00:23:51,680 --> 00:23:53,400
how they lived on the surface.

389
00:23:53,480 --> 00:23:55,920
You've been down here,
working by yourself, all alone?

390
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:59,360
My family, through the millennia...

391
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:02,320
For the last 300 years, just me.

392
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:07,440
I never meant to harm your child.

393
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:12,640
Malohkeh, I rather love you.

394
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:17,720
It's safe. We can wake him.

395
00:24:21,760 --> 00:24:23,680
(MALOHKEH CHUCKLES)

396
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:28,320
Come.

397
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:35,360
- Elliot? ELl, it's Dad.
- What...? Dad.

398
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:42,280
- You're safe now.
- But where are we?

399
00:24:42,360 --> 00:24:46,000
Well,
I've got to be honest with you, son.

400
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:48,000
We're in the centre of the Earth...

401
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:49,680
and there are lizard men.

402
00:24:53,240 --> 00:24:55,000
- Hi.
- Wow.

403
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:59,000
Elliot, I'm sorry.

404
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:01,280
I took my eye off you.

405
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:05,080
It's OK. I forgive you.

406
00:25:08,160 --> 00:25:09,960
You go on, Doctor. I'll catch up.

407
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:15,280
PA: Storage facility 19 operational.

408
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:37,960
We lived on the surface of the planet
long before you did.

409
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:41,400
Our sole purpose has been
to return to our rightful place.

410
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:42,600
And we've got a planet

411
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:45,120
that can't already sustain
the people who live there.

412
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:49,280
And you want to add a whole other
species, to drain resources...

413
00:25:49,360 --> 00:25:53,720
ELDANE: As I sat there that day
across the table from the humans,

414
00:25:53,840 --> 00:26:00,280
the future of both species and of our
beloved planet Earth rested in our hands.

415
00:26:00,360 --> 00:26:02,160
But as the discussions went on,

416
00:26:02,280 --> 00:26:06,640
I began to despair about whether
we would ever find any common ground.

417
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:12,440
As ambassadors for our species,
we all had too much to lose.

418
00:26:12,520 --> 00:26:16,360
So, erm, what about the areas
that aren't habitable to us?

419
00:26:16,440 --> 00:26:18,960
Australian outback,

420
00:26:19,040 --> 00:26:23,360
Sahara desert, Nevada plains...

421
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:26,720
- They're all deserted.
- Yes, fine, but what happens

422
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:30,240
when their population
grows and breeds and spreads?

423
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:32,640
And anyway,
what benefit does humanity get,

424
00:26:32,720 --> 00:26:35,600
and how will we ever sell this
to people on the surface?

425
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:38,720
If I could get a word in,
maybe I could tell you.

426
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:43,200
You give us space,
we can bring new sources of energy,

427
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:48,800
new methods of water supply,
new medicines, scientific advances.

428
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:50,760
We were a great civilisation.

429
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:52,960
You provide a place
for us on the surface,

430
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:57,840
we'll give you knowledge and
technology beyond humanity's dreams.

431
00:26:57,920 --> 00:27:02,960
We work together,
this planet could achieve greatness.

432
00:27:04,880 --> 00:27:09,240
OK. Now I'm starting to see it.

433
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:11,400
- Oh, yeah.
- (APPLAUSE)

434
00:27:13,360 --> 00:27:15,000
Not bad for a first session.

435
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:17,600
More similarities than differences.

436
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:19,880
(WHOOSHING)

437
00:27:19,960 --> 00:27:23,840
The transport has returned.
Your friends are here.

438
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:28,880
That's not right.

439
00:27:34,600 --> 00:27:35,960
What are you doing?!

440
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:43,200
Protecting our race
against the apes.

441
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:45,040
You can't do this!

442
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:48,560
You're a good scientist, Malohkeh,
but this is war.

443
00:27:51,560 --> 00:27:53,520
Argh!

444
00:27:57,640 --> 00:27:59,040
Here they are.

445
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:05,320
Mum!

446
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:07,800
AMY: Rory!

447
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:10,320
Something's wrong...

448
00:28:12,720 --> 00:28:14,720
AMY: Doctor, what's he carrying?

449
00:28:17,160 --> 00:28:19,280
No.

450
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:23,480
Don't do this.
Tell me you didn't do this.

451
00:28:38,600 --> 00:28:40,320
What did you do?

452
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:42,760
It was me.

453
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:47,440
- I did it.
- Mum?

454
00:28:47,520 --> 00:28:48,680
I just wanted you back.

455
00:28:57,720 --> 00:28:59,000
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

456
00:28:59,080 --> 00:29:02,200
You have to believe me,
they're better than this.

457
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:05,280
- This is our planet!
- We had a chance here.

458
00:29:05,360 --> 00:29:06,200
Leave us alone.

459
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:09,520
In future, when you talk about this,
you tell people there was a chance

460
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:14,960
but you were so much less
than the best of humanity.

461
00:29:27,320 --> 00:29:29,480
My sister.

462
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:44,680
(SHE WAILS)

463
00:29:56,680 --> 00:30:00,160
And you want us
to trust these apes, Doctor?

464
00:30:00,240 --> 00:30:02,520
One woman.

465
00:30:02,600 --> 00:30:04,920
She was scared for her family.
She's not typical.

466
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:06,160
I think she is.

467
00:30:06,240 --> 00:30:10,040
One person let us down.
But there's a whole race of dazzling,

468
00:30:10,120 --> 00:30:13,320
peaceful human beings up there.

469
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:16,800
You were building something here.
Come on, an alliance could work.

470
00:30:18,560 --> 00:30:20,160
It's too late for that, Doctor.

471
00:30:23,760 --> 00:30:25,840
Why?

472
00:30:25,920 --> 00:30:27,520
Our drill

473
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:31,840
is set to start
burrowing again in...

474
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:33,440
15 minutes.

475
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:37,600
- What?
- What choice did I have? They had Elliot.

476
00:30:37,680 --> 00:30:40,800
- Don't do this, don't call their bluff.
- Let us go back.

477
00:30:40,880 --> 00:30:43,680
And you promise to never come
to the surface ever again.

478
00:30:43,760 --> 00:30:46,000
We'll walk away, leave you alone.

479
00:30:47,560 --> 00:30:50,560
- Execute her.
- No!

480
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:53,320
Everybody, back to the lab! Run!

481
00:30:53,400 --> 00:30:56,360
Execute all the apes!

482
00:30:56,440 --> 00:30:59,480
This is a deadly weapon - stay back.

483
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:09,000
Take everyone to the lab!

484
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:17,120
- I'll cover you!
- RORY: Go! Go!

485
00:31:19,760 --> 00:31:23,640
Ah-ah! Stop right there! Or I'll
use my very deadly weapon again.

486
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:25,920
One warning, that's all you get.

487
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:29,120
If there can be no deal, you go back
into hibernation. All of you. Now.

488
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:31,840
This ends here.

489
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:34,800
No. It only ends with our victory.

490
00:31:34,880 --> 00:31:36,520
Like I said...

491
00:31:36,600 --> 00:31:39,520
one warning.

492
00:31:45,920 --> 00:31:48,880
Elliot, you and your dad
keep your eyes on that screen.

493
00:31:48,960 --> 00:31:50,320
Let me know if we get company.

494
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:52,520
Amy, keep reminding me
how much time I haven't got.

495
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:54,520
OK, 12%2 minutes till drill impact.

496
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:58,760
Tony Mack, sweaty forehead,
dilated pupils, what're you hiding?

497
00:31:58,840 --> 00:32:01,200
Tony! What happened?!

498
00:32:01,280 --> 00:32:03,960
Alaya's sting.
She said there's no cure.

499
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:06,160
I'm dying, aren't I?

500
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:10,160
- You're not dying, you're mutating.
- How can I stop it?

501
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:12,320
Decontamination program!
Might work - don't know.

502
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:14,440
Eldane, can you run
the program on Tony?

503
00:32:14,520 --> 00:32:18,680
Doctor, shed load of those
creatures coming our way!

504
00:32:18,760 --> 00:32:20,360
We're surrounded in here!

505
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:22,400
So, question is,
how do we stop the drill,

506
00:32:22,480 --> 00:32:24,560
given that we can't
get there in time? Plus also,

507
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:26,320
how do we get out,
given that we're surrounded?

508
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:28,520
How do you feel about
an energy pulse,

509
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:30,760
channel led up through the tunnels
to the base of the drill?

510
00:32:30,840 --> 00:32:33,440
- To blow up my life's work?
- Yes.

511
00:32:33,520 --> 00:32:35,800
Sorry. No nice way of putting that.

512
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:37,800
Right, well,

513
00:32:37,880 --> 00:32:40,840
you're going to have to do it
before the drill hits the city, in...

514
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:42,520
- 11 minutes, 40 seconds...
- Yes!

515
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:46,040
- Squeaky bum time!
- Yes, but the explosion

516
00:32:46,120 --> 00:32:47,640
is going to cave in
all the surrounding tunnels,

517
00:32:47,720 --> 00:32:49,960
so we have to be on the surface by then.

518
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:53,720
- But we can't get past Restac's troops.
- I can help with that...

519
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:56,760
Toxic Fumigation -

520
00:32:56,840 --> 00:33:01,480
an emergency failsafe meant to
protect my species from infection.

521
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:04,360
A warning signal to occupy cryo-chambers.

522
00:33:04,480 --> 00:33:09,840
After that, citywide fumigation,
by toxic gas. Then the city shuts down.

523
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:14,280
You could end up killing your own people.

524
00:33:14,360 --> 00:33:17,000
Only those foolish enough
to follow Restac.

525
00:33:17,080 --> 00:33:19,000
Eldane, are you sure about this?

526
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:22,120
My priority is my race's survival.

527
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:24,440
The Earth isn't ready
for us to return yet.

528
00:33:24,520 --> 00:33:26,480
- No.
- Ten minutes, Doctor.

529
00:33:26,560 --> 00:33:28,840
But maybe it should be.
So here's a deal.

530
00:33:28,920 --> 00:33:30,640
Everybody listening.

531
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:32,400
Eldane, you activate shutdown...

532
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:34,880
I'll amend the system,
set your alarm for 1,000 years' time.

533
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:38,880
1,000 years, to sort the planet out.
To be ready. Pass it on.

534
00:33:38,960 --> 00:33:43,880
As legend, or prophecy, or religion,
but somehow, make it known.

535
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:48,600
- This planet is to be shared.
- Yeah. I get you.

536
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:54,920
- Nine minutes, seven seconds.
- Yes, fluid controls, my favourite!

537
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:57,600
Energy pulse timed, primed and set.

538
00:33:57,680 --> 00:34:01,360
Before we go, energy barricade,
need to cancel it out - quickly.

539
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:04,240
(HIGH-PITCHED WHINING)

540
00:34:04,320 --> 00:34:05,840
Fumigation pre-launching.

541
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:10,200
There's not much time for us to get
from here to the surface, Doctor!

542
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:11,840
Ah-ha, super-squeaky bum time!

543
00:34:11,920 --> 00:34:14,040
Get ready to run for your lives.
Now...

544
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:18,160
But the decontamination program
on your friend hasn't started yet.

545
00:34:20,160 --> 00:34:24,120
Well, go. All of you! Go.

546
00:34:24,200 --> 00:34:26,960
- No, we're not leaving you here!
- Granddad!

547
00:34:27,040 --> 00:34:28,560
Eight minutes, ten seconds.

548
00:34:28,640 --> 00:34:30,720
Now, you look after your mum.

549
00:34:33,320 --> 00:34:35,600
You mustn't blame her.

550
00:34:35,680 --> 00:34:37,640
She only did what she thought was right.

551
00:34:37,720 --> 00:34:40,720
I'm not going to see you again, am I?

552
00:34:40,800 --> 00:34:42,920
I'll be here.

553
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:45,480
Always.

554
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:47,400
I love you, boy.

555
00:34:49,040 --> 00:34:52,080
- You be sure he gets home safe!
- This is my fault.

556
00:34:52,160 --> 00:34:54,000
No, I can't go back up there.

557
00:34:54,080 --> 00:34:55,520
I'd be a freaks how.

558
00:34:55,600 --> 00:34:59,120
The technology down here's my only hope.

559
00:35:01,120 --> 00:35:03,760
I love you, Dad.

560
00:35:07,840 --> 00:35:10,160
- Go. Go!
- Come on.

561
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,320
Go on.

562
00:35:18,720 --> 00:35:20,640
Toxic fumigation initiated.

563
00:35:20,720 --> 00:35:22,800
- Return to cryo-chambers.
- No!

564
00:35:22,880 --> 00:35:25,880
- Toxic fumigation initiated.
- No!

565
00:35:25,960 --> 00:35:28,520
- Return to cryo-chambers.
- This is not the order!

566
00:35:28,600 --> 00:35:32,400
- Toxic fumigation initiated.
- They're going! We're clear!

567
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:36,120
OK. Everyone follow Nasreen.
Look for a blue box. Get ready to run.

568
00:35:39,960 --> 00:35:40,920
I'm sorry.

569
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:44,720
I thought for a moment,
our race, and the humans...

570
00:35:44,800 --> 00:35:47,400
Yeah. Me too.

571
00:35:47,480 --> 00:35:49,720
Doctor!
We've got less than six minutes.

572
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:52,360
Go! Go! I'm right behind you!

573
00:35:54,240 --> 00:35:55,800
Let's go.

574
00:35:55,880 --> 00:36:00,560
- I'm not coming either.
- What?

575
00:36:04,640 --> 00:36:06,200
Oh, for goodness' sake!

576
00:36:06,280 --> 00:36:09,000
We're going to hibernate with them,
me and Tony.

577
00:36:09,080 --> 00:36:10,640
Doctor, you must go!

578
00:36:10,720 --> 00:36:12,720
I can be decontaminated
when we're woken.

579
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:16,200
- All the time in the world.
- But...

580
00:36:16,280 --> 00:36:19,080
Nasreen...you...

581
00:36:19,160 --> 00:36:22,000
No. This is perfect.
I don't want to go.

582
00:36:22,080 --> 00:36:23,840
I've got what I was digging for.

583
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:26,600
I can't leave when
I've only just found it.

584
00:36:26,680 --> 00:36:29,280
Doctor!

585
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:30,720
Thank you, Doctor.

586
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:32,320
The pleasure was all mine.

587
00:36:39,320 --> 00:36:41,920
Come and look for us.

588
00:36:46,760 --> 00:36:49,160
(ALARM BLARES)

589
00:36:49,240 --> 00:36:52,360
ELDANE: So, the Doctor sent our warriors
back to their rest

590
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:55,640
on the promise
of future harmony with humans.

591
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:11,200
- Immediate evacuation.
- The other way, idiot!

592
00:37:11,280 --> 00:37:13,760
Toxic fumigation is about to commence.

593
00:37:13,840 --> 00:37:15,800
- Immediate evacuation.
- Come on!

594
00:37:15,880 --> 00:37:18,760
Toxic fumigation
ls about to commence.

595
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:21,440
No questions, just get in!

596
00:37:21,520 --> 00:37:23,080
And yes, I know it's big!

597
00:37:23,160 --> 00:37:26,280
Ambrose, sickbay up the stairs,
left, then left again...

598
00:37:26,360 --> 00:37:30,960
get yourself fixed up. Come on!
Five minutes and counting...

599
00:37:31,040 --> 00:37:35,080
Not here. Not now.
It's getting wider.

600
00:37:35,160 --> 00:37:36,440
The crack on my bedroom wall.

601
00:37:36,520 --> 00:37:38,400
Two parts of space and time

602
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:41,720
that should never
have touched right here.

603
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:45,960
And the Byzantium. All through
the universe - rips in the continuum.

604
00:37:46,880 --> 00:37:48,200
How could it be following me?

605
00:37:48,280 --> 00:37:50,800
Some sort of space-time cataclysm.
An explosion, maybe.

606
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:54,520
Big enough to put cracks
in the universe. But what?

607
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:56,040
Four minutes fifty...
We have to go!

608
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:57,600
The Angels laughed
when I didn't know.

609
00:37:57,680 --> 00:37:59,520
Prisoner Zero knew.
Everybody knows, except me!

610
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:02,440
- Doctor, just leave it.
- But where there's an explosion,

611
00:38:02,520 --> 00:38:04,360
there's shrapnel.

612
00:38:04,440 --> 00:38:07,160
Doctor, you can't put
your hand in there!

613
00:38:07,240 --> 00:38:09,080
Why not?

614
00:38:14,440 --> 00:38:17,320
Ahhh!

615
00:38:22,440 --> 00:38:25,520
- I've got something!
- What is it?

616
00:38:30,920 --> 00:38:32,880
I don't know.

617
00:38:32,960 --> 00:38:35,600
- Doctor!
- (RESTAC GROANS)

618
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:38,200
She was there, when the gas started.

619
00:38:38,280 --> 00:38:39,520
- She must've been poisoned.
- You!

620
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:42,240
- OK, get in the TARDIS, both of you.
- You did this.

621
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:43,440
Doctor!

622
00:38:43,520 --> 00:38:46,280
- (HE SCREAMS)
- Rory!

623
00:38:46,360 --> 00:38:49,000
(RORY GROANS)

624
00:38:51,800 --> 00:38:53,480
Rory, can you hear me?

625
00:38:56,960 --> 00:38:59,360
I don't understand.

626
00:38:59,440 --> 00:39:00,520
Shh-shh. Don't talk.

627
00:39:00,600 --> 00:39:03,360
Doctor, is he OK?
We have to get him onto the TARDIS!

628
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:07,600
We were on the hill.
I can't die here.

629
00:39:07,680 --> 00:39:10,720
Don't say that.

630
00:39:10,800 --> 00:39:13,720
You're so beautiful...

631
00:39:19,200 --> 00:39:20,720
I'm sorry.

632
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:29,680
Doctor, help him.

633
00:39:34,280 --> 00:39:37,560
If the time energy catches up with you,
you'll never have been born.

634
00:39:37,640 --> 00:39:39,640
It will erase every moment
of your existence.

635
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:42,520
You will never have lived at all.

636
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:44,000
Amy, move away from the light.

637
00:39:44,080 --> 00:39:46,680
If it touches you,
you'll be wiped from history.

638
00:39:46,760 --> 00:39:48,560
Amy, move away now.

639
00:39:48,640 --> 00:39:51,480
No! I am not leaving him!
We have to help him!

640
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:52,880
The light's already around him,

641
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:55,120
- we can't help him.
- I am not leaving him!

642
00:39:55,200 --> 00:39:56,200
- We have to.
- No.

643
00:39:56,280 --> 00:39:57,440
- Sorry!
- Get off me!

644
00:39:57,520 --> 00:39:59,120
- Sorry!
- Get off me!

645
00:40:00,640 --> 00:40:02,080
No!

646
00:40:02,160 --> 00:40:04,760
No! No! No!

647
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:10,360
Let me out, please let me out.
I need to get to Rory.

648
00:40:16,960 --> 00:40:22,720
That light - if his body's absorbed

649
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:28,360
I'll forget him. He'll never have
existed. You can't let that happen.

650
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:32,280
What are you doing?

651
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:35,760
- Doctor! No!
- (METALLIC THRUMMING)

652
00:40:40,640 --> 00:40:44,880
No! No! Doctor,
we can't just leave him there.

653
00:40:44,960 --> 00:40:45,920
Keep him in your mind.

654
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:48,120
Don't forget him. If you forget him,
you'll lose him forever.

655
00:40:48,200 --> 00:40:50,320
On the Byzantium,
I still remembered the Clerics

656
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:52,240
because I am a time traveller,
now you said.

657
00:40:52,320 --> 00:40:53,760
They weren't part of your world.

658
00:40:53,840 --> 00:40:56,240
This is different...
this is your own history changing.

659
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:58,160
Don't tell me it's going to be OK.

660
00:40:58,240 --> 00:40:59,200
You have to make it OK.

661
00:40:59,280 --> 00:41:01,800
It's going to be hard,
but you can do it, Amy.

662
00:41:01,880 --> 00:41:03,320
Tell me about Rory.

663
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:07,200
Fantastic Rory,
funny Rory, gorgeous Rory.

664
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:09,800
Amy, listen to me.
Do exactly as I say.

665
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:12,600
Amy, please.
Keep concentrating. You can do this.

666
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:16,520
- I can't.
- You can.

667
00:41:16,600 --> 00:41:19,160
You can do it.
I can't help you unless you do.

668
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:25,560
Come on. We can still save his memory.
Come on, Amy. Please...

669
00:41:26,560 --> 00:41:29,000
(INAUDIBLE)

670
00:41:29,080 --> 00:41:31,320
Come on, Amy, come on.

671
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:36,240
Amy, please.
Don't let anything distract you.

672
00:41:37,760 --> 00:41:39,640
Oh-oh!

673
00:41:39,720 --> 00:41:42,040
Argh!

674
00:41:42,120 --> 00:41:45,920
Remember Rory. Keep remembering,
Rory is only alive in your memory.

675
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:47,560
You must keep hold of him.

676
00:41:47,640 --> 00:41:49,280
Don't let anything distract you.

677
00:41:49,360 --> 00:41:51,440
Rory still lives in your mind.

678
00:41:51,520 --> 00:41:52,920
(SLAMMING)

679
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:03,680
What were you saying?

680
00:42:10,560 --> 00:42:14,080
I have seen some things today,
but this is beyond mad.

681
00:42:14,160 --> 00:42:15,600
Doctor!

682
00:42:15,680 --> 00:42:17,480
Five seconds till it all goes up!

683
00:42:33,360 --> 00:42:35,920
All Nasreen's work just erased.

684
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:37,720
Good thing she's not here to see it.

685
00:42:37,800 --> 00:42:40,480
She's going to give Tony hell
when they wake up.

686
00:42:44,040 --> 00:42:47,000
You could've let
those things shoot me.

687
00:42:48,400 --> 00:42:51,520
- You saved me.
- An eye for an eye.

688
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:54,760
It's never the way.

689
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:58,600
Now you show your son
how wrong you were.

690
00:42:58,680 --> 00:43:00,400
How there's another way.

691
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:03,760
You make him the best of humanity...

692
00:43:05,640 --> 00:43:07,680
...in the way you couldn't be.

693
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:31,440
You're very quiet.

694
00:43:31,520 --> 00:43:34,800
Oh! Hey! Look! There I am again!
(SHOUTS) Hello, me!

695
00:43:39,120 --> 00:43:41,960
Are you OK?

696
00:43:42,040 --> 00:43:44,560
I thought I saw someone else
there for a second.

697
00:43:48,520 --> 00:43:51,560
I need a holiday.
Didn't we talk about Rio?

698
00:43:51,640 --> 00:43:56,880
You go in.
Just fix this lock, keeps jamming.

699
00:43:58,120 --> 00:44:00,200
You boys and your locksmithery.

700
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:07,200
ELDANE: Now as my people awaken
from their 1,000-year sleep

701
00:44:07,280 --> 00:44:08,960
ready to rise to the surface,

702
00:44:09,040 --> 00:44:14,280
my thoughts turn back to the Doctor,
the losses he suffered then

703
00:44:14,360 --> 00:44:17,560
and the greater losses
that were still to come.

